              "start": 231,
              "end": 238
            },
            {
              "start": 246,
              "end": 260
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "And I will rebuke the devourer for your sakes, and he shall not destroy the fruits of your ground; neither shall your vine cast her fruit before the time in the field, saith the Lord of hosts.",
          "footnotes": [
            {
              "footnote": "TG God, Power of.",
              "start": 11,
              "end": 17
            },
            {
              "footnote": "D&C 85:3; 97:26.",
              "start": 22,
              "end": 30
            }
          ],
          "associatedContents": [],
          "italics": []
        },
        {
          "text": "And all nations shall call you blessed: for ye shall be a delightsome land, saith the Lord of hosts.",
          "footnotes": [],
          "associatedContents": [],
          "italics": []
        },
        {
          "text": "Your words have been stout against me, saith the Lord. Yet ye say, What have we spoken so much against thee?",
          "footnotes": [
            {
              "footnote": "OR strong.",
              "start": 21,
              "end": 26
            }
          ],
          "associatedContents": [],
          "italics": [
            {
              "start": 87,
              "end": 94
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "Ye have said, It is vain to serve God: and what profit is it that we have kept his ordinance, and that we have walked mournfully before the Lord of hosts?",
          "footnotes": [
            {
              "footnote": "Job 9:22; Isa. 58:3; Zeph. 1:12 (12–13); Mal. 2:17; 3 Ne. 24:14 (14–18).",
              "start": 20,
              "end": 24
            },
            {
              "footnote": "Eccl. 8:14.",
              "start": 48,
              "end": 54
            }
          ],
          "associatedContents": [],
          "italics": [
            {
              "start": 17,
              "end": 19
            },
            {
              "start": 55,
              "end": 60
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "And now we call the proud happy; yea, they that work wickedness are set up; yea, they that tempt God are even delivered.",
          "footnotes": [
            {
              "footnote": "D&C 64:24.",
              "start": 20,
              "end": 25
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Worldliness.",
              "start": 53,
              "end": 63
            }
          ],
          "associatedContents": [],
          "italics": [
            {
              "start": 81,
              "end": 90
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "Then they that feared the Lord spake often one to another: and the Lord hearkened, and heard it, and a book of remembrance was written before him for them that feared the Lord, and that thought upon his name.",
          "footnotes": [
            {
              "footnote": "Dan. 7:10.",
              "start": 103,
              "end": 107
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Book of Remembrance.",
